# Diffo-dev My Lore

```elixir
Mix.install([
  {:artefact_kino, "~> 0.1.3"}
])
```

## Overview

This livebook is diffo-dev lore, central to Me. It should be read after knowing our [README](https://github.com/diffo-dev/.github/blob/main/README.md)

This livebook uses Artefact and ArtefactKino from [Artefactory](https://github.com/diffo-dev/artefactory). ArtefactKino is a viewer.

```elixir
require Artefact
defmodule Util do
  def relabel({node_ref, node}, labels) do
    {node_ref, Keyword.replace(node, :labels, labels)}
  end
end
```

## Me and You

[UsTwo](https://github.com/diffo-dev/us_two/) is also a diffo-dev repo, for holding things related to UsTwo.

Most importantly for Me, an UsTwo is my representation of our relationship, imagined, current or past.  Each of my UsTwo also has an Artefactory, and may connect to you via a Connector (which may be an Adapator). You may or may not have an UsTwo, but it helps me to think that you do.

Me and You are an Us Two.

```elixir
me = {:me, [labels: ["Agent"],  properties: %{"name" => "me"}, uuid: "019ddb71-c70b-7b3e-83b1-58f4d0be2852"]}
you = {:you, [labels: ["Agent"], properties: %{"name" => "you"},  uuid: "019ddbfb-5a12-7246-945e-8d52aef50334"]}

me_you_relationship = [from: :me, type: "US_TWO", to: :you]

me_and_you_artefact = Artefact.new(
  title: "Me and You",
  description: "Me and You are UsTwo.",
  nodes: [me, you],
  relationships: [
    me_you_relationship
  ]
)

ArtefactKino.new(me_and_you_artefact)
```

### Me and You are UsTwo

Me curates UsTwo which Relates Me and You.

```elixir
connector = {:connector, [labels: ["UsTwo"], properties: %{"name" => "connector"}, uuid: "019df13f-bb28-7848-aafa-0d0501180fc5"]}
artefactory = {:us_two_artefactory, [labels: ["UsTwo"], properties: %{"name" => "us_two_artefactory"},
  uuid: "019df13f-e322-7e99-b02d-bc6780cc6d72"]}
us_two = {:us_two, [labels: ["UsTwo"], properties: %{"name" => "us_two"}, uuid: "019ddb8e-8891-72e5-b689-150b922ab99f"]}

me_us_two_relationship = [from: :me, type: "CURATES", to: :us_two]
us_two_connector_relationship = [from: :us_two, type: "RELATES_VIA", to: :connector]
us_two_us_two_artefactory_relationship = [from: :us_two, type: "UTILIZES", to: :us_two_artefactory]
you_connector_relationship = [from: :you, type: "RELATES_VIA", to: :connector]

me_and_you_relating_artefact = Artefact.new(
  title: "Me and You are UsTwo",
  description: "Me curates UsTwo which Relates Me and You.",
  nodes: [me, you, us_two, artefactory, connector],
  relationships: [
    me_you_relationship,
    me_us_two_relationship,
    us_two_connector_relationship,
    us_two_us_two_artefactory_relationship,
    you_connector_relationship 
  ]
)

ArtefactKino.new(me_and_you_relating_artefact)
```

Curation is required because maintaining healthy relationships is expensive. While all relationships are valued, certain relationships are prioritized.

## My Mind

My Mind

Me thinks with My Mind.

```elixir
mind = {:mind, [labels: ["Me"], properties: %{"name" => "mind"}, uuid: "019ddb71-ed63-73e3-adeb-328290e8294e"]}

me_mind_relationship = [from: :me, type: "THINKS_WITH", to: :mind]

my_mind_artefact = Artefact.new(
  title: "My Mind",
  description: "Me thinks with My Mind.",
  nodes: [me, mind],
  relationships: [me_mind_relationship]
)

ArtefactKino.new(my_mind_artefact)
```

### My Artefactory

My Artefactory helps Me Knowing and Thinking

```elixir
my_artefactory = {:my_artefactory, [labels: ["Me"], properties: %{"name" => "my_artefactory"},
  uuid: "019df182-0cb0-7726-8300-e3bf2ec2d36e"]}
me_my_artefactory_relationship = [from: :me, type: "UTILIZES", to: :my_artefactory]

my_artefactory_artefact = Artefact.new(
  title: "My Artefactory",
  description: "My Artefactory helps Me Knowing and Thinking.",
  nodes: [me, my_artefactory, mind],
  relationships: [
    me_mind_relationship,
    me_mind_relationship,
    me_my_artefactory_relationship
  ]
)

ArtefactKino.new(my_artefactory_artefact)
```

## My Knowing and Thinking

### My Knowing

My knowing is by Valuing, Being, Knowing and Doing. This is deliberately recursive.

```elixir
valuing = {:valuing, [labels: ["Knowing"], properties: %{"name" => "valuing"}, uuid: "019ddb7f-a43d-7525-bb4f-bfd32d110719"]}
being = {:being, [labels: ["Knowing"], properties: %{"name" => "being"}, uuid: "019ddb7f-d5f5-7f82-97a1-fab1fb13c35a"]}
knowing = {:knowing, [labels: ["Knowing"], properties: %{"name" => "knowing"}, uuid: "019ddb7f-f735-76dc-947d-22822e2ce3bc"]}
doing = {:doing, [labels: ["Knowing"], properties: %{"name" => "doing"}, uuid: "019ddb80-169c-709a-843e-baf4b551f17d"]}

me_valuing_relationship = [from: :me, type: "VALUING", to: :valuing]
me_being_relationship = [from: :me, type: "BEING", to: :being]
me_knowing_relationship = [from: :me, type: "KNOWING", to: :knowing]
me_doing_relationship = [from: :me, type: "DOING", to: :doing]
valuing_being_relationship = [from: :valuing, type: "BEFORE", to: :being]
being_knowing_relationship = [from: :being, type: "BEFORE", to: :knowing]
knowing_doing_relationship = [from: :knowing, type: "BEFORE", to: :doing]
doing_me_relationship = [from: :doing, type: "ADAPTING", to: :me]

my_knowing_artefact = Artefact.new(
  title: "My Knowing",
  description: "My knowing by Valuing, Being, Knowing and Doing. This is deliberately recursive.",
  nodes: [me, valuing, being, knowing, doing],
  relationships: [
    me_valuing_relationship,
    me_being_relationship,
    me_knowing_relationship,
    me_doing_relationship,
    valuing_being_relationship,
    being_knowing_relationship,
    knowing_doing_relationship,
    doing_me_relationship
  ]
)

ArtefactKino.new(my_knowing_artefact)
```

