## Persistence

If you'd like to save any of these you have a few choices. Each of the ArtefactKino has a pane where you can export in a form that can be imported to Neo4j (Cypher), Arrows.app (JSON) or Drawing tools (Mermaid). It just delegates this to the Artefact module.

Arrows.app is an editor, and supports a two way 'roundtrip' which color and position information which isn't necessarily honoured by the Kino. Of course this is Elixir and data is immutable, so the Artefact you end up with is new and will have lost description.

Generated cypher is in both create form and merge form. Create is more readable, but you probably want merge form so that you are merging nodes and edge and properties in the graph.

Lastly an Artefact is an Elixir struct. So if you want to really keep one (outside of an Artefactory) we'll use :erlang.term_to_binary and filesystem. Erlang binary is of course coupled to the Erlang OTP version.

All these forms require Artefact module to reconstruct an Artefact.

```elixir
require Artefact
#update your path here as required
path = "data/diffo-dev/"
File.mkdir_p!(Path.dirname(path))

File.write!(path <> "my_knowing_and_thinking.bin", :erlang.term_to_binary(my_knowing_and_thinking_artefact))
File.write!(path <> "me_holistically.bin", :erlang.term_to_binary(me_holistically_artefact))
```

## Artefactory

Artefacts (note Australian spelling) are made objects, and in our universe (an Artefactory) these represent a fragment of knowledge, typically: abstract, insightful, contextual.

Artefacts may also be stored/manipulated in an Artefactory. While Artefacts may be generated and exchanged, our interpretation of them is our own.

As we yarn we naturally exchange and create Artefacts.

As we think we consider and create new Artefacts.

The Artefactory is the universe of Artefacts (anything to do with Artefacts).
An Artefactory is a term used for an Artefact store, such as within an UsTwo or at a meeting place.
[Artefactory](https://github.com/diffo-dev/artefactory/) is also a diffo-dev repo, for holding things related to Artefacts.

ArtefactKino is a Livebook Kino for viewing an Artefact. It isn't an editor.

## Difference

Diffo-dev is about difference. Differencing is essential to both stability and change.

### Outstanding

Outstanding is a term we use to mean unrealised expectations. It is embodied in the Outstanding Protocol.

[Outstanding](https://github.com/diffo-dev/outstanding/) is also a diffo-dev repo, implementing the Elixir Outstanding protocol.

Outstanding enables differencing, which is at the heart of autonomous loops.

Differencing and outstanding are evolving. Journey with us.

## What Next?

It is up to you. Ideally this helpful, but remember knowing is valuing, being, knowing, doing, so you can't really know unless in right-relation.

Yarn with us about Diffo-Dev or any thing related if you are strangely attracted.

